<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-271-085  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 271 085.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Jan 23 1989 v23 n3 p25(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Let's jail the virus makers. (Soft Talk) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Barnes, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The media-made image of a computer virus maker as a frustratedgenius is inaccurate and blocks solution of the problem.andP;  Virusmakers are second-rate thinkers with large egos.andP;  They plantviruses to feed their egos.andP;  The physical means of securingsystems exists in terms of limiting access and following knownprocedural precautions.andP;  Virus makers must be portrayed as anuisance rather than a clever threat in order to be stopped.andP;  Thewriters of virus-catching software should be portrayed as thegeniuses.andP;  Virus makers should also be given punishmentcommensurate with the crime.andP;  Damage in the millions of dollarsshould warrant time behind bars.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer virusesComputer CrimeSecurityCritiqueIssues-SocietyComputer industry.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>